    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a concours-grade 996.2 Carrera 4S, featuring the venerable 3.6L flat-six mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. This example remains in factory-fresh condition, with the M96 powerplant benefitting from a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recent bore scope inspection confirming zero cylinder scoring. The wide-body chassis retains its structural rigidity, supported by a factory-tuned suspension and massive four-piston monobloc calipers. Finished in flawless paint with zero rock chips, the undercarriage is equally immaculate, showcasing original heat shields and pristine exhaust headers. A true collector-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
